# Impeccable

> The vocabulary you didn't know you needed. 1 skill, 18 commands, and curated
> anti-patterns for impeccable frontend design.

Impeccable builds on Anthropic's `frontend-design` skill with deeper expertise
and more control. Every LLM learned from the same generic templates — without
guidance, you get predictable mistakes: Inter font, purple gradients, cards
nested in cards, gray text on colored backgrounds. Impeccable fights that bias.

---

## Domain Reference Files

| Reference            | Covers                                                        |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| typography           | Type systems, font pairing, modular scales, OpenType          |
| color-and-contrast   | OKLCH, tinted neutrals, dark mode, accessibility              |
| spatial-design       | Spacing systems, grids, visual hierarchy                      |
| motion-design        | Easing curves, staggering, reduced motion                     |
| interaction-design   | Forms, focus states, loading patterns                         |
| responsive-design    | Mobile-first, fluid design, container queries                 |
| ux-writing           | Button labels, error messages, empty states                   |

When handling a design task, load the relevant reference(s) before producing output.

---

## 18 Commands

### Setup & Planning
| Command               | What it does                                                 |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/impeccable teach`   | One-time setup: gather design context, save to config        |
| `/impeccable craft`   | Full shape-then-build flow with visual iteration             |
| `/impeccable extract` | Pull reusable components and tokens into the design system   |

### Audit & Review
| Command    | What it does                                                        |
|------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/audit`   | Run technical quality checks (a11y, performance, responsive)        |
| `/critique`| UX design review: hierarchy, clarity, emotional resonance           |

### Polish & Shipping
| Command    | What it does                                                        |
|------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/polish`  | Final pass, design system alignment, and shipping readiness         |
| `/distill` | Strip to essence — remove complexity                                |
| `/harden`  | Add error handling, onboarding, i18n, edge cases                    |

### Visual Refinement
| Command     | What it does                                                       |
|-------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/clarify`  | Improve unclear UX copy                                            |
| `/optimize` | Performance improvements                                           |
| `/animate`  | Add purposeful motion                                              |
| `/colorize` | Introduce strategic color                                          |
| `/bolder`   | Amplify boring designs                                             |
| `/quieter`  | Tone down overly bold designs                                      |
| `/delight`  | Add moments of joy                                                 |
| `/adapt`    | Adapt for different devices                                        |
| `/typeset`  | Fix font choices, hierarchy, sizing                                |
| `/layout`   | Fix layout, spacing, visual rhythm                                 |
| `/overdrive`| Add technically extraordinary effects                              |

### Command Usage

Most commands accept an optional argument to focus on a specific area:

```
/audit blog              # Audit blog hub + post pages
/audit dashboard         # Check dashboard components
/critique landing page   # Review landing page UX
/polish feature modal    # Clean up modal before release
/distill checkout        # Strip checkout form to essentials
/animate hero            # Add motion to hero section
/typeset headers         # Fix heading hierarchy and fonts
/layout sidebar          # Fix sidebar spacing and rhythm
```

**Combining commands** — chain for full workflows:
```
/audit /normalize /polish blog      # Full workflow: audit → fix → polish
/critique /harden checkout          # UX review + add error handling
```

**When to use each:**
- `/audit` — before making changes, to understand what needs fixing
- `/normalize` — after audit, to fix inconsistencies against design system
- `/critique` — when you want design feedback, not technical fixes
- `/polish` — last step before deploying to production

---

## Anti-Patterns — What NOT to Do

These are explicit signals of AI-generated "slop" design. Never produce or
recommend any of the following:

### Typography
- ❌ Overused fonts: Arial, Inter (as a default), system-ui as sole choice
- ❌ Too many font weights on one page
- ❌ Line lengths over 75ch in body text
- ❌ Skipping heading levels (h1 → h3 with no h2)

### Color & Contrast
- ❌ Gray text on colored backgrounds (contrast fails)
- ❌ Pure black (`#000000`) or pure gray — always use tinted neutrals
- ❌ Purple gradients (overused AI default)
- ❌ Dark glows as decorative elements

### Layout & Spacing
- ❌ Cards nested inside cards
- ❌ Wrapping everything in card components
- ❌ Cramped padding (touch targets under 44px)
- ❌ Side-tab borders as the only visual differentiator

### Motion
- ❌ Bounce or elastic easing — feels dated and unprofessional
- ❌ Motion with no purpose (decoration only)
- ❌ Ignoring `prefers-reduced-motion`

### General AI Slop Signals
- ❌ Generic hero sections with stock-photo backgrounds
- ❌ "Get Started" as the only CTA label
- ❌ Three-column feature grids as the default layout
- ❌ Testimonial carousels with star ratings

---

## CLI Anti-Pattern Detector

Impeccable includes a standalone CLI that detects 24 issues across AI slop and
general design quality — without needing an AI harness:

```bash
npx impeccable detect src/                   # scan a directory
npx impeccable detect index.html             # scan an HTML file
npx impeccable detect https://example.com    # scan a URL (Puppeteer)
npx impeccable detect --fast --json .        # regex-only, JSON output
```

Catches: side-tab borders, purple gradients, bounce easing, dark glows,
excessive line length, cramped padding, small touch targets, skipped headings,
and more.

---

## Orchestration Logic

When the user triggers this skill:

1. **Identify the command** — map user intent to the closest command above
2. **Load relevant references** — based on the area being worked on:
   - Typography issues → load `typography` reference
   - Color/contrast issues → load `color-and-contrast` reference
   - Animation work → load `motion-design` reference
   - Layout/spacing → load `spatial-design` reference
   - Form/interactive elements → load `interaction-design` reference
   - Mobile/responsive → load `responsive-design` reference
   - Copy/labels → load `ux-writing` reference
3. **Check for anti-patterns** — before producing output, verify none of the
   anti-patterns listed above will appear in the result
4. **Produce output** — apply the command logic with reference guidance
5. **For `/audit` or `/critique`** — produce a structured report with:
   - Issues found (severity: critical / warning / info)
   - Specific element + evidence
   - Recommended fix
   - No edits made (report only)
6. **For `/polish` or `/normalize`** — apply fixes directly, then summarize
   what changed and why

---

## Output Format

### Audit / Critique Reports

```
## Audit: [Area]

### Critical
- [Element]: [Issue] → Fix: [Action]

### Warning
- [Element]: [Issue] → Fix: [Action]

### Info
- [Element]: [Observation]

### Anti-patterns Detected
- [Pattern name]: found in [location]
```

### Design Fixes (polish, normalize, etc.)

Produce the corrected code, then append a brief summary:

```
## Changes Made
- Typography: switched from Inter to [font] for [reason]
- Color: replaced #808080 on blue to [tinted neutral] for WCAG AA compliance
- Spacing: increased padding from 8px to 16px on [component]
```

---

## Critical Rules

1. **Never use pure defaults** — always make deliberate typographic, color, and
   spacing choices. No Inter-on-white-card by default.
2. **Tint your neutrals** — pure grays are forbidden. Use OKLCH or HSL with
   slight hue shift matching the brand color.
3. **Earn every animation** — motion must serve a purpose. If you can't explain
   why it helps the user, remove it.
4. **Mobile-first always** — start from the smallest viewport and expand up.
5. **Accessible by default** — WCAG AA minimum on all text. Test focus states.
6. **Anti-patterns are hard stops** — if producing output would introduce a
   listed anti-pattern, stop and choose an alternative approach.
7. **Design system first** — always check for existing tokens/components before
   creating new ones.
